1b) Foucalt’s Pendulum

The pendulum swings in all directions depending on the force acting on it. If earth were moving, it could only move in one direction! https://t.co/5t5SZYbyFI

2) Ships & Horizon 

Here globers find themselves in a predicament:

If the Z axis curves while the X axis doesn’t, that would make a cylinder.

Also, the curve can’t be so gentle u can’t c it at 120K ft, but so dramatic a ship goes over it. Pick 1 false premise pls. https://t.co/Gc0ppMw4Ch

A nice globe debunk. If an ant were walking on an orange, the viewer could see the surface curving in all directions

Because an orange is a sphere

But earth is not https://t.co/COMeugxhV4

Constellations debunk the globe. We couldn’t see the same stars year-round if we were orbiting thru space.

Discrepancies in shadows are caused by the distance of the object from the sun, or the sun’s movement across the sky.
